What you need to know:

The priest’s journey in the country started in Ol Kalou, where he stayed for 14 years before moving to the sun-baked Kinamba in Ng’arua, Laikipia County.Here, his name is deeply etched in the people’s memories for helping them sink boreholes, thus helping them ease their perennial water scarcity.Now aged 71, his sermons oscillate between English and local languages – Kiswahili and Kikuyu, depending on the message of the day.